==Abstract==

This IIP describes the Bech32 address format for INTcoin. It adapts BIP 173 with INTcoin-specific prefixes.

==Motivation==

Bech32 provides:
* Error detection with BCH codes
* Case-insensitive encoding
* Efficient QR code representation
* Clear separation from legacy formats

==Specification==

===Format===

<pre>
<hrp>1<data><checksum>
</pre>

Where:
* hrp = Human-readable part (network prefix)
* 1 = Separator
* data = Base32-encoded witness version and program
* checksum = 6-character BCH checksum

===Human-Readable Parts===

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Network !! HRP !! Example
|-
| Mainnet || int || int1q...
|-
| Testnet || tint || tint1q...
|-
| Signet || sint || sint1q...
|-
| Regtest || rint || rint1q...
|}

===Witness Version===

INTcoin uses witness version 1 (Bech32m encoding):
* Version 1: Native post-quantum addresses

===Address Construction===

<pre>
address = bech32m_encode(hrp, [version] + convertbits(program, 8, 5))
</pre>

Where program is SHA3-256(public_key).

===Character Set===

Base32 alphabet: qpzry9x8gf2tvdw0s3jn54khce6mua7l

===Checksum===

Bech32m uses the constant 0x2bc830a3 (vs Bech32's 0x01).

===Address Length===

INTcoin addresses are approximately 62 characters:
* HRP: 3-4 characters
* Separator: 1 character
* Version: 1 character
* Program: 52 characters (32 bytes in base32)
* Checksum: 6 characters

